    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a two-level hierarchical structure with 8 parent categories (mobile OS distributions) and 2 detailed drilldown series. Synthetic data was generated using market simulation parameters: parent categories follow a power-law distribution (\u03bc=12.3%, \u03c3=14.8), while version distributions exhibit Pareto principles (80/20 rule). Data integrity was maintained through automated sum validation (drilldowns match parent totals \u00b10.1%). The column chart was selected for its effectiveness in comparing categorical proportions, optimized through Tufte's data-ink principles by removing gridlines and using minimal contrasting colors. Cairo's perceptual topology is implemented through sequential color gradients and proportional width encoding. Accessibility features include ARIA label generation and keyboard-navigable drill paths, with statistical validity demonstrated through synthetic distribution modeling (parent \u03bc=12.3%, \u03c3=14.8; child \u03bc=3.1%, \u03c3=6.4)."
